2667:+The clearest treatment-biomarker-outcome structure in this cohort centers on treatment_venetoclax_azacitidine: response is concentrated in unfit_for_intensive and npm1_mutation subgroups, while tp53_mutation and complex_karyotype blunt or eliminate the apparent benefit. General disease burden and functional status markers behave as expected, with worse ECOG status, marrow blasts, WBC, CRP, and weight loss associated with lower response and albumin associated with higher response. The FLT3 and IDH targeted therapy indicators did not show the anticipated positive mutation-matched response patterns in these data. Because these are observational EHR-derived records, the findings should be read as associations rather than causal treatment effects.`;
